{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-article-js","path":"/academy/blog/posts/deriv-multipliers-how-they-work/","result":{"data":{"directus":{"blog":[{"id":"e7aee366-c2c2-4204-987f-b72604f3f6e6","blog_title":"Deriv multipliers: How they work","meta_title":"Deriv multipliers: How they work","meta_description":"Find out what are multipliers, how you can amplify potential profits, and how trading with Deriv multipliers is different from leverage trading.","og_title":"Multipliers: Here's how they work","og_description":"Find out what are multipliers, how you can amplify potential profits, and how trading with Deriv multipliers is different from leverage trading.","published_date":"2021-09-15","read_time_in_minutes":2,"blog_post":"<p>Trading with leverage allows you to take a larger position in the market with a small amount of capital. However, leveraged trading also comes with the possibility of large losses.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Not on Deriv multipliers.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Multipliers allow you to amplify your potential profits in a similar way as leveraged trading. You simply apply a multiplier to your trades to potentially multiply your profit. But unlike leveraged trading, you won&rsquo;t be increasing your potential losses at the same time.</p>\n<h2>How multipliers work</h2>\n<p>Here&rsquo;s an example. Let&rsquo;s say you trade with a stake of 100 USD and predict the market will go up. The market then goes up by 2%.</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.7709%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 48.3604%; height: 150px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p><strong>Without a multiplier</strong>, your profit is:</p>\n<p>2% x 100 USD = <strong>2 USD</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 48.3604%; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p><strong>With a x500 multiplier</strong>*, your profit is:</p>\n<p>2% x 100 USD x 500 = <strong>1,000 USD</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>On the other hand, your losses are limited to your stake when trading multipliers on Deriv. For example:&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.7691%; border-style: none; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"text-align: center;\">\n<td style=\"width: 300px; height: 150px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #000000;\">\n<p>On <strong>leveraged trading with 1:500* leverage</strong>, your loss is:</p>\n<p>2% x (100 USD x 500) = <strong>1,000 USD</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 300px; height: 150px; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; border: 1px solid #000000;\">Regardless of the multiplier you choose, the stop out feature will limit your loss to your stake of <strong>100 USD.</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*multiplier values and leverage differ per country you&rsquo;re trading in</p>\n<h2>Benefits of trading with multipliers</h2>\n<h3>Ramp up your trades</h3>\n<p>Add a multiplier to your trades &mdash; the higher the multiplier, the higher your potential profits. (If you reside in the EU or UK, your multiplier values are pre-determined based on the asset you&rsquo;re trading.)</p>\n<h3>Limit your risk</h3>\n<p>Risk losing no more than your initial stake with the automatic stop out function &mdash; on every single trade.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Manage the possibilities</h3>\n<p>Secure your profit automatically, protect your stake, and feel free to change your mind with <a href=\"https://deriv.com/academy/blog/posts/risk-management-features-on-deriv-multipliers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">risk-management features</a> like take profit, stop loss, and deal cancellation.</p>\n<h3>Trade anytime, anywhere</h3>\n<p>Trade multipliers on <a href=\"https://deriv.com/academy/blog/posts/what-is-forex-live-trading/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">forex</a>, <a href=\"https://deriv.com/academy/blog/posts/cryptocurrency-trading-for-beginners-on-deriv/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">cryptocurrencies</a>, and Deriv&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://deriv.com/academy/blog/posts/an-introduction-to-synthetic-indices-trading/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">synthetic indices</a> on both desktop and on Deriv&rsquo;s mobile app, Deriv GO. With crypto and synthetic indices available to trade 24/7 even on weekends, you can trade multipliers anytime, anywhere you want.</p>\n<p>Find out how to get started trading multipliers on Deriv&rsquo;s DTrader trading platform in this <a href=\"https://deriv.com/academy/blog/posts/how-to-trade-multipliers-on-dtrader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">step-by-step guide</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Disclaimer:</em></p>\n<p><em>Deriv GO is not available for clients residing in the EU and the UK.</em></p>\n<p><em>Multipliers trading on cryptocurrencies is not available for clients residing in the UK.</em></p>\n<p><em>The deal cancellation feature is not available on multipliers on cryptocurrencies for users residing within the EU.</em></p>","author":{"id":"0d7772f6-5338-488f-a8aa-adfb6c5074b9","name":"The Deriv team","image":{"id":"9826d676-357b-4683-8f80-28a4ef931f91","description":"Deriv Logo","imageFile":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/move-to-deriv/static/2efee03fa50ea098c4f945ea8267e57d/de3a1/9826d676-357b-4683-8f80-28a4ef931f91.png","srcSet":"/move-to-deriv/static/2efee03fa50ea098c4f945ea8267e57d/f2a56/9826d676-357b-4683-8f80-28a4ef931f91.png 38w,\n/move-to-deriv/static/2efee03fa50ea098c4f945ea8267e57d/7458e/9826d676-357b-4683-8f80-28a4ef931f91.png 75w,\n/move-to-deriv/static/2efee03fa50ea098c4f945ea8267e57d/de3a1/9826d676-357b-4683-8f80-28a4ef931f91.png 150w","sizes":"(min-width: 150px) 150px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/move-to-deriv/static/2efee03fa50ea098c4f945ea8267e57d/0852d/9826d676-357b-4683-8f80-28a4ef931f